headline.main: British Win Fifth Gold in World Track Cycling Championships

snippet: Bradley Wiggins and Mark Cavendish provided a rip-roaring climax to the five-day world track cycling championships in London with a stunning victory in the Madison event that gave Britain a table-topping fifth gold medal.
lead_paragraph: Bradley Wiggins and Mark Cavendish provided a rip-roaring climax to the five-day world track cycling championships in London with a stunning victory in the Madison event that gave Britain a table-topping fifth gold medal.
